 orchestration — rendering is entirely your responsibility.",[164,171,175],{"className":172,"icon":173,"title":174},[167],"noto:building-construction","Single Source of Truth","Form state lives in one canonical object.\nNo duplicated mirrors, no hidden caches, no divergence between “view state” and “data state”.",[164,177,181],{"className":178,"icon":179,"title":180},[167],"noto:top-hat","Explicity Over Implicit Magic","No hidden proxies, no auto-registration side effects.\nEvery field, mutation, and validation step is deliberate and traceable.",[164,183,187],{"className":184,"icon":185,"title":186},[167],"noto:puzzle-piece","Isolation/Modularization","Core logic, framework bindings, and utilities are separated by design.\nEach layer can evolve independently without leaking abstractions.",[164,189,193],{"className":190,"icon":191,"title":192},[167],"noto:locked-with-key","Type Safety Focused","Deep path inference, compile-time validation, and structural guarantees.\nIf a field path compiles, it exists.",[164,195,199,200,210],{"className":196,"icon":197,"title":198},[167],"noto:test-tube","Opt-in Standard Validation","Validation is pluggable and schema-driven.\nAdopt ",[201,202,206],"a",{"href":203,"rel":204},"https://standardschema.dev/",[205],"nofollow",[207,208,209],"code",{},"StandardSchemaV1"," when needed — stay lightweight when not.",[164,212,216],{"className":213,"icon":214,"title":215},[167],"noto:triangular-ruler","Determinism Over Convenience","No surprising mutations. No implicit resets.\nGiven the same inputs, the system behaves the same way — always.",[164,218,222,223,228,229,234],{"className":219,"icon":220,"title":221},[167],"noto:globe-showing-asia-australia","Framework-Agnostic","Works with ",[201,224,227],{"href":225,"rel":226},"https://react.dev/",[205],"React",", ",[201,230,233],{"href":231,"rel":232},"https://vuejs.org/",[205],"Vue",", or anything else.\nThe core does not depend on a rendering model.",[164,236,240],{"className":237,"icon":238,"title":239},[167],"noto:crossed-swords","Battle-Tested","Used in complex, deeply nested, dynamic form scenarios.\nDesigned to handle real-world edge cases without collapsing under scale.",[156,242,243,246],{},[103,244,245],{"v-slot:title":95},"Available For",[103,247,248,266,278],{"v-slot:features":95},[249,250,254,263],"u-page-feature",{"icon":251,"target":252,"to":253},"mdi:language-javascript","_blank","https://www.npmjs.com/package/@goodie-forms/core",[103,255,256,257],{"v-slot:title":95},"@goodie-form/core ",[258,259,262],"span",{"className":260},[261],"text-primary","JavaScript",[103,264,265],{"v-slot:description":95},"With FormController, it is possible to manage your form states and attach DOM elements.",[249,267,269,275],{"icon":51,"target":252,"to":268},"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@goodie-forms/react",[103,270,271,272],{"v-slot:title":95},"@goodie-form/react - ",[258,273,227],{"className":274},[261],[103,276,277],{"v-slot:description":95},"With exposed hooks, it is possible to use Goodie Forms without leaving your React environment.",[249,279,281,287],{"icon":140,"target":252,"to":280},"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@goodie-forms/vue",[103,282,283,284],{"v-slot:title":95},"@goodie-form/vue - ",[258,285,233],{"className":286},[261],[103,288,289],{"v-slot:description":95},"[WIP] Not available yet.",{"title":95,"searchDepth":291,"depth":291,"links":292},2,[],"md",{},true,"/",{"title":298,"description":299},"Goodie Forms - An unopinionated modern form state and data management library","Goodie Forms is a modern, unopinionated form state and data management library for TypeScript apps. Create flexible, type-safe forms with complete control over validation and state.","index","EkOeQx3SZ1XWj5gQeAiR91mpGHG0Tugw2fUBI-cfaXQ",1772223570939]